Class Series

java.lang.Object
ib.grapher.Series
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<Cell>
public class Series extends Object implements Iterable<Cell>
A class which loosely "holds" any number of Cells in a doubly linked list. As well as calculating a statistical report of the series and holding references to its first and last Cells, a Series also contains an iterator to make it easier to loop through the whole series at once.

  • Constructor Details

    • Series

      public Series(int cells)
      A constructor that initializes this series, as well as adding a set number of empty cells to it. All series should always have at least one cell in them at all times.
      Parameters:
      cells - The number of cells to be added. This should be at least 1. If it is 0 or less, it will be ignored.

      public void save()
      Saves this series header to the output file, overwriting an existing entry for the series. If this series has not yet been added, FileDataManager.encodeForInsertion(Series) should be used instead.
